---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<section class="early-life section-padding" id="early-life">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Ecuador to Chicago -->
    <div class="origin-grid">
      <div class="origin-text">
        <span class="section-label animate-in" data-i18n="meet.origin_label">The Journey</span>
        <h2 class="section-title animate-in" data-i18n="meet.origin_headline">From Ecuador to Chicago: Forged by Struggle</h2>
        
        <p class="early-paragraph animate-in" data-i18n="meet.origin_p1">
          Byron Sigcho-Lopez was born and raised in Quito, Ecuador. At 17, after a tragic car accident left his mother in a coma, his family insisted he leave the country to finish his education. He arrived in Tennessee alone, knowing no one and speaking no English. A generous local family took him in and helped him pursue an education.
        </p>
        
        <p class="early-paragraph animate-in" data-i18n="meet.origin_p2">
          Byron earned a soccer scholarship, received an honorable mention for the All-State Tennessee Soccer Team, and graduated from Cumberland University with a B.A. in Mathematics and Business Administration, earning the prestigious President's Award. After graduation, he moved to Chicago and settled in Pilsen to start his life.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="origin-image-wrap animate-in">
        <img 
          src={`${base}/images/early-life-placeholder.png`} 
          alt="Byron teaching in a community classroom in Pilsen"
          class="origin-image"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Political Awakening -->
    <div class="awakening-section">
      <div class="awakening-divider">
        <span class="awakening-year animate-in">2013</span>
        <div class="awakening-line"></div>
        <span class="awakening-tag animate-in" data-i18n="meet.awakening_tag">The Turning Point</span>
      </div>

      <div class="awakening-grid">
        <div class="awakening-text">
          <h3 class="awakening-headline animate-in" data-i18n="meet.awakening_headline">The Political Awakening</h3>
          
          <p class="early-paragraph animate-in" data-i18n="meet.awakening_p1">
            In Chicago, Byron became an adult education teacher at the University of Illinois at Chicago and founded UIC's Center for Literacy Spanish literacy program, making the GED accessible to Spanish-speaking immigrants. He also volunteered as a youth soccer coach at Pilsen Academy and earned his Master's in Economics from UIC.
          </p>
          
          <p class="early-paragraph animate-in" data-i18n="meet.awakening_p2">
            As a lead researcher at UIC, he collaborated with the Chicago Teachers Union to investigate the financial relationships between charter school networks, school funding, and Chicago's political elite. He organized alongside parents and teachers like Karen Lewis to fight for fully funded public schools.
          </p>
          
          <p class="early-paragraph animate-in" data-i18n="meet.awakening_p3">
            When Rahm Emanuel announced the closure of over 130 Chicago Public Schools, the largest mass school closing in American history, Byron stepped up. He joined the Pilsen Alliance and eventually served as its director for a decade, organizing community meetings, leading protests, and spearheading referendums to fight gentrification, displacement, and corruption.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .early-life {
    background: var(--cream);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .early-life::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: -100px;
    right: -100px;
    width: 350px;
    height: 350px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(5, 173, 237, 0.05) 0%, transparent 70%);
    border-radius: 50%;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  /* Origin Grid */
  .origin-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-4xl);
    align-items: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4xl);
  }

  .origin-image-wrap {
    position: relative;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
  }

  .origin-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 420px;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
  }

  .early-paragraph {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--gray-700);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .early-paragraph:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Awakening Divider */
  .awakening-section {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .awakening-divider {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .awakening-year {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--orange);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .awakening-line {
    flex: 1;
    height: 3px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--orange), transparent);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .awakening-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--orange);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .awakening-headline {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 900;
    line-height: 1.1;
    color: var(--blue);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .origin-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-2xl);
    }

    .origin-image {
      height: 280px;
    }

    .awakening-divider {
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .awakening-line {
      order: 3;
      width: 100%;
    }
  }
</style>
